The GeoSphere is based on the [Three.js](http://www.threejs.com) polysphere. However it is more than just a 3d model -- in fact it does not directly render 3D graphics. What it does is to model the points and proximities of points on a tessellated sphere at multiple levels of depth. 

This data is all centralized around a ?[Planet](planet) class. The Planet has an array of vertices that are organized into 


* * * * *

&apos; perhaps 8 on a really fast machine.